NAME

  **echo** - echo command line args to the terminal

SYNOPSIS

    echo [...]

DESCRIPTION

    The echo command will immediately output all of its arguments
    to the terminal, then return. Each argument will be space-
    separated, and the last argument will be followed by a newline.
    When passed no arguments, echo will raise an error.

OPTIONS

    -h, --help:  output usage information and exit

SEE ALSO

    [cat](/data/man/cat.dsmd), [splash](/data/man/splash.dsmd)